Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Defendant will comply with all federal, and state laws, and local alcohol, drug and violence ordinances during the period of this Agreement.  If there is a case charging a violation of a criminal statute or local ordinance pending when this agreement is due to expire, this agreement continues in effect until 30 days after such case is revolved.  If the Defendant is charged with a criminal offense in a case subsequent to the Court's approval of this agreement, a finding of probable cause in that case is sufficient basis for termination of this agreement. Defendant will continue to comply with all bail or bond conditions ordered by the Court while this agreement is in effect. 
Pay a fine of misdemeanor court costs within 120 days of the date of his plea, unless a payment plan is approved by the Clerk of Courts. 
Pay restitution in the amount of $693.94, which defendant stipules he or she owes in this matter, not including the 10% surcharge. $400 cash bail has been posted, the pareis will recommend that the $400 cash bail be converted to a $1000 signature bond and the $400 posted will immediately be disbursed to the victim.  This will leave a balance owing of $234.94, which defendant agrees to pay no later than six months from the date of this plea. Restitution will be joint and several with the co-defendant in Douglas County juvenile file 22JV49.
No later than 60 days from the date of this plea, the defendant will write letters of apology to each victim in this matter. The letters will be provided to the DA's office no later than 60 days from the date of this plea.  This will not constitute a violation of the no contact condition of his bail.
The defendant will complete 100 hours of community service by December 31, 2022. The community service will be for a non-profit organization in Douglas County, Wisconsin.
Comply with all conditions of probation in this file relative to Counts 2, 3 and 5.

AND PLEA/SENTENCING 8:41 AM Defendant Kaden James Tuura in court.  Attorney Chris A Gramstrup in court for Kaden James Tuura.  Attorney Mark Adam Fruehauf in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Gramstrup received information, waives reading and has a plea agreement. State recites agreement that defendant plead to Count 1, 2, 3, and 5. Counts 4, 6 and 7 are dismissed but read in. For Count 1, a deferred judgement of conviction for a 2 year period. For Counts 2, 3 and 5, a withheld sentence for 2 years probation. Concurrent on each case. Conditions of probation include comply with all programming as deemed necessary by the Dept of Corrections, pay mandatory court costs, restitution in amount of $643.94 joint and several with 22JV49, continuation of no contact order, write letters of apology to victims and complete 100 hours of community service to be monitored by probation. State has complied with Victim's Rights. For Count 1, 2, 3, and 5 defendant pleads no contest. For Count 1, court accepts the Defendant's plea and finds that the Defendant's plea has been freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.  The Defendant understands all the rights he is waiving by his plea.  The Defendant is found guilty and Judgment of Conviction is deferred pursuant to the terms of the agreement.   For Counts 2, 3 and 5, Attorney Hansen stipulates to a factual basis. Court accepts the Defendant's plea and finds that the Defendant's plea has been freely, voluntarily and intelligently made. The Defendant understands all the rights he is waiving by his plea. The Defendant is found guilty and Judgment of Conviction is entered.

Court imposes for Count 2, a withheld sentence for 2 years probation. Concurrent on each case. Conditions of probation include comply with all programming as deemed necessary by the Dept of Corrections, pay mandatory court costs, restitution in amount of $643.94 joint and several with 22JV49, continuation of no contact order, write letters of apology to victims and complete 100 hours of community service to be monitored by probation. For Count 3, a withheld sentence for 2 years probation. Concurrent probation and conditions on each case. Conditions of probation include comply with all programming as deemed necessary by the Dept of Corrections, pay mandatory court costs, restitution in amount of $643.94 joint and several with 22JV49, continuation of no contact order, write letters of apology to victims and complete 100 hours of community service to be monitored by probation. For Count 5, a withheld sentence for 2 years probation. Concurrent on each case. Conditions of probation include comply with all programming as deemed necessary by the Dept of Corrections, pay mandatory court costs, restitution in amount of $643.94 joint and several with 22JV49, continuation of no contact order, write letters of apology to victims and complete 100 hours of community service to be monitored by probation. Court amends to a $2,000 signature bond with same conditions and bail to be applied.
